WEBVTT

00:15.050 --> 00:19.280
[anticipatory music]
[wind whooshing]

00:20.100 --> 00:23.060
[electricity crackling]

00:28.630 --> 00:32.470
[electricity humming]

00:32.670 --> 00:37.600
[text clacking]
[dynamic music]

00:43.390 --> 00:46.040
[ethereal music]

00:53.140 --> 00:55.540
[birds chirping]

00:55.740 --> 01:00.620
[gentle music]
[guests chattering]

01:04.890 --> 01:07.450
[rings clinking]

01:32.480 --> 01:34.230
[Woman] You look stunning.

01:34.430 --> 01:37.360
- I still can't believe
how fast his day's come.

01:37.560 --> 01:40.100
[music continues]

01:50.020 --> 01:52.200
[Hardin] "Love is patient.

01:52.400 --> 01:53.370
Love is kind.

01:54.720 --> 01:57.290
It does not envy and
it does not boast.

01:58.240 --> 01:59.460
It's not proud.

02:00.380 --> 02:02.470
It does not dishonor others.

02:02.670 --> 02:03.730
It's not self-seeking.

02:04.680 --> 02:06.830
It is not easily angered,

02:07.030 --> 02:08.730
and it keeps no
record of wrongs.

02:09.950 --> 02:11.390
Love does not delight in evil,

02:13.000 --> 02:14.520
but rejoices with the truth.

02:16.740 --> 02:20.060
It always protects,
always trusts,

02:20.260 --> 02:23.090
always hopes and
always perseveres.

02:24.140 --> 02:25.750
Love never fails."

02:31.760 --> 02:35.160
But I failed us, Tess.

02:35.360 --> 02:38.340
- [Tessa] How long have
you been writing about us?

02:38.540 --> 02:41.590
[soft melancholy music]

02:42.550 --> 02:44.650
[Hardin] After we kissed.

02:44.850 --> 02:45.730
Are you fucking kidding me?

02:45.930 --> 02:48.220
[Hardin] Where are you going?

02:48.420 --> 02:49.480
I'm done.

02:49.680 --> 02:50.780
We're just a bomb
waiting to explode.

02:50.980 --> 02:52.440
This was a wake up call.

02:52.640 --> 02:55.140
You would never let me read
what you were writing in there,

02:55.340 --> 02:56.750
and now the whole world gets to!

02:56.950 --> 02:58.920
- I never meant for
it to be published.

02:59.120 --> 03:01.530
Fuck, this never should
have happened like this.

03:01.730 --> 03:02.930
You accidentally wrote a book,

03:03.130 --> 03:04.710
and then you shopped it around

03:04.910 --> 03:07.450
to publishers without asking me.

03:07.650 --> 03:10.150
- What is the point in
everything we've been through

03:10.350 --> 03:12.630
if we can't channel that into
something that helps people?

03:12.830 --> 03:13.980
It's never too late.

03:14.180 --> 03:15.290
People can always change.

03:15.490 --> 03:18.160
That is the kind of
story "After" is.

03:18.360 --> 03:19.670
"After?"

03:20.460 --> 03:22.240
- It's my journey
after I met you.

03:24.850 --> 03:27.120
I think that journey's over.

03:27.320 --> 03:32.080
[Tessa's voice echoing]
[solemn music]

03:32.770 --> 03:34.000
[air whooshing]
[door closes]

03:34.200 --> 03:35.610
- [Hardin] My failure
was thinking

03:35.810 --> 03:39.210
that I was writing
my journey, my story,

03:41.430 --> 03:42.870
but it was our story, Tess.

03:43.700 --> 03:46.440
[solemn music]

04:03.330 --> 04:04.420
[objects rummaging]

04:04.620 --> 04:05.810
But I know our story
isn't finished.

04:07.290 --> 04:09.730
Even if you've moved on,
[drawer slams]

04:09.930 --> 04:10.680
I can't.

04:12.730 --> 04:14.210
I can't imagine my
world without you

04:16.030 --> 04:18.250
because without you
there is only me,

04:20.650 --> 04:22.270
broken,

04:22.470 --> 04:23.260
lost,

04:24.300 --> 04:25.130
and alone.

04:26.610 --> 04:27.440
Without you,

04:29.310 --> 04:31.140
I have no after.

04:31.340 --> 04:33.230
[music intensifies]

04:33.430 --> 04:36.150
[music fades]

04:36.350 --> 04:40.070
♪ Do you feel let go

04:40.270 --> 04:41.980
♪ Oh

04:42.180 --> 04:46.160
♪ When the lights get low

04:46.360 --> 04:48.210
♪ Oh

04:48.400 --> 04:49.380
Welcome.

04:49.580 --> 04:50.990
Can I get you a table?

04:51.190 --> 04:52.860
I might have one.

04:53.060 --> 04:53.900
Hi, darling.

04:55.250 --> 04:56.070
Katherine.

04:58.120 --> 05:00.000
- It's a wonder I could
get you outta the house.

05:00.200 --> 05:01.910
Hopefully all that time

05:02.110 --> 05:03.350
you spent holed
up in there means

05:03.550 --> 05:04.950
you're closing in on a draft?

05:06.690 --> 05:07.780
I'll do a whiskey.

05:09.350 --> 05:10.870
And I'll do an Aperol spritz.

05:12.350 --> 05:15.450
Hardin, everyone at
Dowlish is dying to see it,

05:15.650 --> 05:19.060
and I'm afraid I can't
keep putting people off,

05:19.260 --> 05:21.530
not if we're gonna make
it to print by Christmas.

05:22.530 --> 05:23.890
- You know, Harper
Lee didn't publish

05:24.090 --> 05:25.810
her second novel
for 55 years, so-

05:26.010 --> 05:28.510
- People's attention spans are
like fruit flies these days.

05:28.710 --> 05:32.290
You're hot right now, but we
have to ride the "After" wave.

05:32.490 --> 05:35.640
Otherwise it's another
10 months, two years,
whatever it is,

05:35.840 --> 05:37.330
they'll forget you ever existed.

05:39.200 --> 05:40.300
Seems fickle.

05:40.500 --> 05:41.520
Yeah, it is.

05:41.720 --> 05:42.910
You have a tiny
window of relevance

05:43.110 --> 05:44.780
and it's dwindling every day.

05:44.980 --> 05:46.870
Can't rush greatness can you?

05:47.070 --> 05:48.050
I can when I've given you

05:48.250 --> 05:50.090
a quarter million
dollar advance.

05:50.290 --> 05:51.040
It was pounds.

05:53.170 --> 05:56.130
[ice cubes rattling]

05:57.660 --> 05:58.960
I thought you were sober?

06:01.920 --> 06:02.750
I was.

06:04.490 --> 06:05.800
Cheers.

06:06.000 --> 06:08.290
[glasses clinking]

06:08.480 --> 06:11.460
[upbeat music]
[singer singing indistinctly]

06:11.660 --> 06:13.900
- Come on, I'm only
here for one night.

06:14.100 --> 06:14.850
Another round.

06:16.150 --> 06:18.300
- I don't think I
can keep up anymore.

06:18.490 --> 06:19.370
Lightweight.

06:21.940 --> 06:23.820
- Nay Nay?
- Teacup?

06:24.020 --> 06:26.650
God, you look amazing.

06:26.850 --> 06:28.830
- [Kat] I went vegan.
- [Naomi] I've been telling you.

06:29.030 --> 06:31.310
- Hardin, this is Naomi.
We went to college together.

06:31.510 --> 06:32.660
Well, not exactly together.

06:32.860 --> 06:33.960
[Kat laughs]

06:34.160 --> 06:35.610
Let's take shots.

06:37.000 --> 06:38.450
Tequila or vodka?

06:38.650 --> 06:39.930
[upbeat music]
[glasses clinking]

06:40.120 --> 06:42.010
[Naomi and Kat] Cheers.

06:45.570 --> 06:49.110
♪ All I need is your love

06:49.310 --> 06:51.190
Oh, that is my shit!

06:53.410 --> 06:58.200
♪ All I need is
your love tonight ♪

07:01.200 --> 07:06.330
♪ All I need is
your love tonight ♪

07:07.600 --> 07:08.870
♪ Woo

07:09.070 --> 07:14.040
♪ All I need is
your love tonight ♪

07:14.910 --> 07:16.700
♪ Is your love

07:16.900 --> 07:20.840
♪ All I need is
your love tonight ♪

07:21.040 --> 07:25.830
[music fades]
[soft melancholy music]

07:38.630 --> 07:42.810
[upbeat club music
playing faintly]

07:48.330 --> 07:51.600
[soft melancholy music]

08:11.530 --> 08:13.190
- Come on.
- Yes, come on.

08:13.390 --> 08:14.310
I don't dance.

08:15.490 --> 08:18.010
Relax, we'll do the dancing.

08:19.540 --> 08:24.370
♪ All I need is
your love tonight ♪

08:27.070 --> 08:28.380
♪ All I need

08:28.580 --> 08:31.940
[soft melancholy music]

09:01.620 --> 09:02.940
♪ All I need

09:03.140 --> 09:03.980
Let's get out of here.

09:04.180 --> 09:05.290
[Tessa] Let's get out of here.

09:05.490 --> 09:07.200
♪ Is your love tonight

09:07.400 --> 09:09.720
[jazzy music]

09:11.630 --> 09:15.860
- That's what I got.
- I'll never let go [laughs].

09:16.060 --> 09:17.210
[Kat] Let's get some music on.

09:17.410 --> 09:18.950
[Naomi] Oh, yeah, nice flat.

09:19.150 --> 09:20.350
- Thank you.
- Mm hm.

09:20.550 --> 09:22.350
[phone vibrating]

09:22.550 --> 09:25.260
[phone beeps]

09:25.460 --> 09:28.400
