to pay the advance back.

11:13.890 --> 11:16.110
Yeah, got it.

11:16.310 --> 11:18.200
♪ I'll take your hand

11:18.400 --> 11:22.030
♪ Under the sand,
under the sand ♪

11:22.230 --> 11:24.380
♪ Claw my nails in your thigh

11:24.580 --> 11:27.780
♪ Under the sand,
under the sand ♪

11:27.980 --> 11:29.950
Meeting with the parents.

11:30.150 --> 11:31.120
This should be fun.

11:32.080 --> 11:33.300
Just the hour late then.

11:36.080 --> 11:37.300
I'm here now.

11:43.390 --> 11:44.310
I'll have a whiskey.

11:47.440 --> 11:48.930
[Hardin sighs]

11:49.130 --> 11:50.280
What?

11:50.480 --> 11:51.720
- When did you start
drinking again?

11:51.910 --> 11:52.930
Oh, it's fine, Mom.

11:53.130 --> 11:54.460
It's all in moderation,
don't worry.

11:54.660 --> 11:56.500
- It doesn't smell
like moderation.

11:56.700 --> 11:58.500
- Not that you ever did much
in the way of parenting,

11:58.700 --> 12:00.030
but I'm not a child.

12:00.230 --> 12:01.250
I can do what I want.

12:01.450 --> 12:02.330
It was one night.

12:07.900 --> 12:08.720
Cheers.

12:10.420 --> 12:11.250
Cheers.

12:12.510 --> 12:14.220
- Hair of the dog
never hurt anyone.

12:14.420 --> 12:16.040
- Just putting off
the inevitable.

12:16.240 --> 12:17.340
Not if I keep at it.

12:19.080 --> 12:21.010
Why are you even here, anyway?

12:21.200 --> 12:23.880
You two gonna run off together?

12:24.080 --> 12:26.350
- [scoffs] Why
would you say that?

12:27.350 --> 12:28.450
We're both happily married.

12:28.650 --> 12:29.710
Are you?

12:29.910 --> 12:31.280
[Hardin smirks]

12:31.480 --> 12:33.800
- Your father was-
- Wait.

12:34.000 --> 12:35.500
Which father are you
talking about right now?

12:35.700 --> 12:38.010
- Stop being an
asshole to your mom.

12:39.100 --> 12:40.240
I'm here meeting
some board members.

12:40.440 --> 12:41.940
They're talking about me opening

12:42.140 --> 12:45.250
a London branch of
Vance Publishing.

12:45.450 --> 12:47.020
The ever expanding empire.

12:48.500 --> 12:49.730
- I've heard a rumor
that you're nearly

12:49.930 --> 12:53.520
a year behind on delivering
your new manuscript.

12:53.720 --> 12:55.340
- Well, don't believe
everything you hear.

12:55.540 --> 12:56.730
Are you lying to me?

12:57.860 --> 12:59.350
No, I'm not lying.

12:59.550 --> 13:01.380
I was just giving you
some general life advice.

13:03.780 --> 13:05.440
But yeah, to be
fair, in this case,

13:05.640 --> 13:06.750
what you hear does
happen to be true.

13:06.950 --> 13:09.400
- Hardin, what the fuck
is going on with you?

13:09.600 --> 13:11.400
We're just trying to help you.

13:11.600 --> 13:14.050
We can't do that if we
don't know what's going on.

13:15.530 --> 13:17.540
- I don't really know
what's going on either.

13:17.740 --> 13:19.450
I keep on trying to write
and every time I do,

13:19.650 --> 13:22.540
everything just ends
up going back to Tessa.

13:24.100 --> 13:25.720
I keep rewriting the
old stuff, you know?

13:25.920 --> 13:27.770
The same things, what
ifs and hypotheticals

13:27.970 --> 13:29.120
don't really matter
in the end, do they?

13:29.320 --> 13:30.420
Because anyway I look at it,

13:30.620 --> 13:32.290
she's not here and
nothing matters

13:32.490 --> 13:34.030
in this world if
she's not in it.

13:35.200 --> 13:36.340
I don't have another book in me.

13:36.540 --> 13:37.300
I never did.

13:37.500 --> 13:38.560
I think it was all a fluke.

13:38.760 --> 13:40.300
And it's okay if you don't.

13:40.500 --> 13:41.260
You have a gift.

13:41.460 --> 13:42.780
All writers go through this.

13:42.980 --> 13:43.770
Do they?

13:44.860 --> 13:46.000
How the hell would, you know?

13:46.200 --> 13:48.000
You haven't written a
damn thing in your life.

13:49.910 --> 13:52.750
- But I have spent my entire
career finding diamonds

13:52.950 --> 13:56.100
in the slush pile, and I
know talent when I see it.

13:56.300 --> 13:59.540
[phone vibrating]

13:59.740 --> 14:02.370
[Christian sighs]

14:02.570 --> 14:05.070
Look, let me get in
touch with Dowlish

14:05.270 --> 14:06.630
and see if I can do a deal.

14:06.830 --> 14:08.160
- No.
- Ease your deadline.

14:08.360 --> 14:10.330
You can come over to us and
take as long as you need.

14:10.530 --> 14:11.770
We've been over this.

14:11.970 --> 14:13.470
- I don't want to.
- Hardin, if you cannot-

14:13.660 --> 14:15.120
[phone vibrating]

14:15.320 --> 14:16.340
Go on, just go.

14:16.540 --> 14:17.820
- You can't-
- Just go.

14:18.020 --> 14:19.380
You need to.

14:19.580 --> 14:21.860
- I do have to go actually,
because you were late.

14:25.730 --> 14:28.130
- [Trish] No, no, I've
got this, I've got this.

14:28.330 --> 14:29.260
[ice cubes clinking]

14:29.460 --> 14:30.430
Waiter, I'll have another.

14:31.260 --> 14:32.570
I'm around, all right?

14:32.770 --> 14:34.220
If you need me, give me a call.

14:35.350 --> 14:36.840
[hand taps]

14:37.040 --> 14:41.830
[patrons chattering]
[ice cubes clinking]

14:43.970 --> 14:47.410
- You know, a change of scenery
might do you some good,

14:47.610 --> 14:49.880
might be inspiring to just
get out of here for a while.

14:52.150 --> 14:54.720
A bit a distance might
give you new perspective,

14:54.920 --> 14:58.510
might help you make peace with
your past so you can move on.

14:58.710 --> 15:01.330
[solemn music]

15:02.420 --> 15:04.560
I'm not ready to move on yet.

15:04.760 --> 15:08.080
- No, I know, I didn't
mean in regard to...

15:11.690 --> 15:12.560
I meant move forward.

15:14.300 --> 15:15.660
Yeah, just let go of
some of your regrets

15:15.860 --> 15:19.520
so you can stop dragging
them into your future.

15:22.180 --> 15:23.530
I met Nathalie over Christmas.

15:25.480 --> 15:26.360
She asked after you.

15:28.230 --> 15:29.720
How is she?

15:29.910 --> 15:32.070
- Well, we only spoke
for a couple of minutes,

15:32.270 --> 15:33.320
but she seemed good.

15:36.150 --> 15:37.420
She moved to Lisbon.

15:37.620 --> 15:38.540
- Lisbon?
- Mm.

15:39.720 --> 15:41.120
[Trish] Portugal.

15:41.320 --> 15:42.340
I know where Lisbon is, Mom.

15:42.540 --> 15:43.860
I just meant...

15:44.060 --> 15:47.900
- Well, I guess she was
ready for a fresh start.

15:49.160 --> 15:51.770
[energetic music]

15:54.430 --> 15:59.300
♪ What kind of a
person have I become ♪

