Dolce & Gabbana plane ad?

36:46.670 --> 36:48.300
- I'll have a little
scratch and sniff.

36:48.500 --> 36:51.340
- Oh, you are officially out.
- What?

36:51.540 --> 36:52.290
Hey there.

36:54.080 --> 36:56.310
- Oh!
- Oh, God no.

36:56.500 --> 36:57.600
You're gettin' me all wet.

37:00.080 --> 37:01.400
Who's this?

37:01.600 --> 37:02.700
Hardin.

37:02.900 --> 37:06.360
Me and Nat, we grew up together.

37:06.560 --> 37:07.440
Hm.

37:09.740 --> 37:11.010
- [Freya] Grow up,
shake his hand.

37:15.270 --> 37:17.010
Well, this is Sebastian.

37:18.450 --> 37:20.500
Sebastian, Hardin's
in town from London.

37:20.700 --> 37:21.800
He's a famous author.

37:22.970 --> 37:24.810
- Wait, what?
- I wouldn't say famous.

37:25.010 --> 37:25.810
I'm just an author...

37:26.010 --> 37:26.730
No?

37:26.930 --> 37:28.250
Would you say bestselling?

37:28.450 --> 37:29.770
What's one of your books?

37:29.970 --> 37:31.560
- There is only
one, but honestly-

37:31.760 --> 37:32.820
It's called "After."

37:33.020 --> 37:34.210
No way I've heard of that.

37:34.410 --> 37:35.210
I've read that.

37:35.410 --> 37:36.170
[Nathalie] No, you haven't.

37:36.370 --> 37:37.430
I loved it.

37:37.630 --> 37:38.780
Well, as much as you
can love something

37:38.980 --> 37:41.050
that makes you ugly
cry every other page.

37:41.240 --> 37:42.610
- [Maddy] I heard
they're making a movie?

37:42.810 --> 37:43.740
Oh, Harry Style should play you.

37:43.940 --> 37:45.010
Thank you.

37:45.210 --> 37:47.260
- [Maddy] So, you're
working on anything now?

37:48.350 --> 37:49.400
I'm trying, yeah.

37:49.600 --> 37:50.740
What is it they say?

37:52.000 --> 37:54.150
Everyone has one book in them,

37:54.350 --> 37:56.500
only the talented have a second.

37:56.700 --> 37:58.150
Huh, wow.

37:58.350 --> 37:59.670
Spoken like a true writer.

37:59.870 --> 38:01.460
Tell me, where can I
find your body of work?

38:01.660 --> 38:03.590
[girls chuckling]

38:03.790 --> 38:05.850
- The boy can keep up.
- Mm hm.

38:06.050 --> 38:07.590
- You ever been
cliff diving, man?

38:07.790 --> 38:08.940
No, I'm putting my foot down.

38:09.140 --> 38:10.510
You are not roping
him into that.

38:10.710 --> 38:11.990
[Sebastian] What? It's fun.

38:12.190 --> 38:13.900
- It's an accident
waiting to happen.

38:14.100 --> 38:14.850
Come on, man.

38:17.510 --> 38:18.650
Let's do it.

38:18.850 --> 38:23.080
[anticipatory music]
[water splashing]

38:39.490 --> 38:41.020
[suspenseful music]

38:41.220 --> 38:42.630
This is a bad idea.

38:42.830 --> 38:45.460
Seriously Hardin, don't
let him pressure you, okay?

38:45.660 --> 38:48.370
- Yeah man, don't
let me pressure you.

38:48.570 --> 38:51.540
[suspenseful music]

38:53.330 --> 38:54.420
- Woo!
[water splashing]

38:54.620 --> 38:55.510
Let's go!

38:55.710 --> 38:57.300
[suspenseful music]

38:57.500 --> 38:59.560
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

38:59.760 --> 39:01.690
[Nathalie and Maddy] Hardin?

39:01.890 --> 39:03.080
[Freya] Come up.

39:03.280 --> 39:05.950
[music continues]

39:10.210 --> 39:12.050
[water splashing]

39:12.250 --> 39:13.530
[gentle music]

39:13.730 --> 39:15.390
Just fuckin' with you.

39:16.830 --> 39:19.320
[Freya speaking faintly]

39:19.520 --> 39:22.830
[soft melancholy music]

39:29.410 --> 39:32.100
[water gurgling]

39:35.110 --> 39:40.200
[water splashing]
[gentle music]

40:07.920 --> 40:12.800
[Hardin panting]
[music continues]

40:13.620 --> 40:15.800
[waves splashing]

40:24.500 --> 40:27.030
[music swells]

40:40.910 --> 40:42.040
Hardin, hey.

40:46.790 --> 40:49.150
You okay?

40:49.350 --> 40:50.090
Yeah.

40:52.660 --> 40:53.980
Yeah, I will be.

40:54.180 --> 40:58.800
[gentle music]
[seagulls squawking]

41:16.080 --> 41:21.080
[phone vibrating]
[soft music]

41:57.250 --> 42:01.220
Me and Nat, we uh,
we grew up together.

42:01.420 --> 42:04.610
[Hardin's voice echoing]

42:04.810 --> 42:07.560
[anticipatory music]

42:09.040 --> 42:10.490
[keyboard keys clacking]

42:10.690 --> 42:13.700
- [Nathalie] Hardin
was my first crush.

42:14.700 --> 42:18.140
[Nathalie's voice echoing]

42:45.600 --> 42:50.170
[siren wailing faintly]
[music continues]

42:50.780 --> 42:52.960
[phone chimes]

43:02.050 --> 43:03.060
[lock screen clicks]

43:03.260 --> 43:07.970
[Tess sighs]
[phone thuds]

43:10.840 --> 43:13.590
[singer vocalizing]

43:23.470 --> 43:26.770
[pedestrians chattering]

43:43.880 --> 43:45.580
[Hardin] Hey.

43:45.780 --> 43:48.410
- Not much of a
morning person, are we?

43:48.610 --> 43:50.230
- Just haven't had
enough coffee yet.

43:51.800 --> 43:54.200
And I am definitely not a
smoothie person, but thank you.

43:54.400 --> 43:56.200
How can you hate smoothies?

43:56.400 --> 43:57.990
It's literally blended
fruit and a bit of veg.

43:58.190 --> 44:01.160
- It's more about the
aesthetic, isn't it?

44:01.360 --> 44:03.770
It's like a holier than thou
wellness cult kinda thing.

44:09.080 --> 44:10.820
Come on, just try it.

44:12.430 --> 44:13.250
Come on.

44:20.480 --> 44:21.970
Mm, yeah.

44:22.170 --> 44:23.750
Maybe you don't know what
kind of person you are.

44:23.950 --> 44:26.480
[upbeat music]

44:37.890 --> 44:40.540
[water splashing]

44:44.720 --> 44:45.730
Can you do me a favor?

44:45.930 --> 44:47.030
Can you pull in the main sheet?

44:48.720 --> 44:50.040
Pull...

44:50.240 --> 44:51.040
What's the main sheet?

44:51.240 --> 44:52.350
[Nathalie] Sorry, the red one.

44:52.550 --> 44:53.470
Pull the red line.

44:55.250 --> 44:56.910
- I just pull it?
- Yes.

45:00.130 --> 45:01.750
- This okay?
- Yes.

45:01.950 --> 45:03.310
Good.

45:03.510 --> 45:07.740
[wind whistling]
[water splashing]

45:12.620 --> 45:14.240
Here.

45:14.440 --> 45:15.530
You look like you need water.

45:17.540 --> 45:18.360
Thanks.

45:23.540 --> 45:26.820
I've been stuck in my
apartment for so long.

45:27.010 --> 45:28.330
Figure it's taken a toll.

45:29.550 --> 45:30.370
Stuck?

45:32.330 --> 45:33.900
- More like
self-contained, I guess.

45:35.160 --> 45:36.780
Figured if I shut myself
away from the world

45:36.980 --> 45:40.130
for long enough eventually
I'd find the words.

45:40.330 --> 45:42.220
You do like to pick
things apart, don't you?

45:42.420 --> 45:43.440
Oh, yeah.

45:43.640 --> 45:45.350
That's how you get
to the good stuff.

45:46.830 --> 45:48.920
So why do you think
you're struggling so much?

45:50.440 --> 45:52.140
Second novel syndrome.

45:53.830 --> 45:55.280
I mean, it's common
enough to have a name

45:55.480 --> 45:57.050
so at least I'm
not the only one.

45:58.400 --> 46:00.360
But I guess there must
be a number of reasons.

46:02.020 --> 46:03.720
Like?

46:03.920 --> 46:05.070
Picking things apart again?

46:05.270 --> 46:06.110
Oh, yeah.

46:08.150 --> 46:09.370
Well, "After" was easy.

46:11.240 --> 46:12.250
I had my muse.

46:12.450 --> 46:13.560
I was inspired.

46:13.760 --> 46:15.420
I could have written
thousands of pages.

46:16.990 --> 46:18.650
It's kind of the irony
of it all, isn't it?

46:18.850 --> 46:21.090
If I didn't have her, I
wouldn't have the book,

46:21.290 --> 46:24.820
but if I didn't have the book,
then I would still have her.

46:25.560 --> 46:27.310
Oh, she didn't like the book?

46:27.510 --> 46:30.440
- She absolutely
fucking hated the book.

46:30.640 --> 46:32.320
The parts that she read, anyway.

46:32.510 --> 46:33.750
It was more about
the circumstances

46:33.950 --> 46:35.840
of how she read
them as well, but-

46:36.040 --> 46:38.760
- Wait, you didn't ask her
permission to write it?

46:38.960 --> 46:42.280
- I really thought that sharing
our story would help people

46:42.480 --> 46:44.070
the same way that it helped me

46:44.270 --> 46:45.850
to get through my shit
and figure things out,

46:46.050 --> 46:49.160
but obviously I now understand
that I shouldn't have gone

46:49.360 --> 46:50.940
and published it to the
entire fucking world

46:51.140 --> 46:52.810
without telling her,
I know that now.

46:54.500 --> 46:58.250
- I mean, it's not nice being
exposed without your consent.

46:59.420 --> 47:01.170
[Nathalie sighs]

47:01.370 --> 47:05.910
[gentle music]
[water splashing]

47:18.960 --> 47:19.830
Do you see that?

47:21.220 --> 47:22.100
There?

47:23.920 --> 47:25.450
That is my dream.

47:29.670 --> 47:31.810
I think I would wake
up every morning

47:32.010 --> 47:34.460
with the biggest smile on
my face if that was my view.

47:37.200 --> 47:38.070
Seems lonely.

47:40.940 --> 47:45.520
- Nah, not if you have the
right person share it with.

47:45.720 --> 47:48.120
[gentle music]

48:00.090 --> 48:02.540
I don't want to lose this.

48:02.740 --> 48:04.050
I don't either.

48:12.280 --> 48:13.760
So, are you ever gonna show me

48:13.960 --> 48:14.770
what you're writing in there?

48:14.970 --> 48:15.810
I...

48:16.010 --> 48:17.890
Maybe, someday.

48:20.500 --> 48:21.330
Someday.

48:28.550 --> 48:32.960
[singer vocalizing]
[upbeat music]

48:33.160 --> 48:37.400
♪ I know what you
are looking for ♪

48:37.600 --> 48:38.660
Here we are, ladies.

48:38.860 --> 48:39.660
- Oh, yes.
- Oh!

48:39.860 --> 48:41.440
Someone got some sun.

48:41.640 --> 48:44.010
- It's a wonder I'm
still standing actually.

48:44.210 --> 48:46.670
She practically dragged me
down the entire coastline.

48:46.870 --> 48:48.230
- Please, you make it sound
like I made you

48:48.430 --> 48:49.370
sail across the Atlantic.

48:49.560 --> 48:52.020
Mm, let's go dance.

48:52.220 --> 48:55.720
[Maddy chuckles]

48:55.920 --> 48:56.670
You wanna join?

48:58.150 --> 48:59.330
- No, you don't
have to babysit me.

48:59.530 --> 49:01.320
- Come on, Hardin,
have fun with us!

49:04.240 --> 49:05.560
I didn't catch that.

49:05.750 --> 49:08.430
- Oh, I think they want
you to come and dance.

49:08.630 --> 49:10.260
- I think you're gonna
have to send my apologies.

49:10.460 --> 49:12.000
[Nathalie chuckles]

49:12.200 --> 49:14.950
[indistinct singing]

49:18.600 --> 49:21.560
- [Sebastian] I
thought you left town.

49:23.170 --> 49:24.090
I'm still here.

49:25.220 --> 49:26.050
For how long?

49:26.830 --> 49:29.670
[Hardin splutters]

49:29.870 --> 49:30.790
You're lucky, you know?

49:32.010 --> 49:32.830
Why is that?

49:33.840 --> 49:34.660
She's too good.

49:36.190 --> 49:38.410
Definitely too good for you
after the shit you pulled.

49:40.540 --> 49:42.680
When she first got
here, she was a mess.

49:42.880 --> 49:43.630
There was nothing.

49:46.200 --> 49:48.760
We spent a lot of time together
that first year talking.

49:53.290 --> 49:55.170
I know who you are.

49:55.370 --> 49:57.340
She never said your
name, but I can tell.

50:00.510 --> 50:03.610
If it were up to me, you'd
be rotting in a cell.

50:03.810 --> 50:08.910
[pensive music]
[upbeat music playing]

50:10.180 --> 50:11.530
What did you say to him?

50:11.730 --> 50:16.620
[singer vocalizing]
[music continues]

50:17.310 --> 50:18.150
♪ Somethin' about ya

50:18.350 --> 50:19.370
Whiskey, a shot.

50:19.570 --> 50:21.190
[Bartender] Yes, Sir.

50:23.800 --> 50:24.590
Again.

50:24.790 --> 50:27.380
♪ Somethin' about ya, babe.

50:27.580 --> 50:28.410
Mm hm.

50:31.280 --> 50:35.300
♪ Somethin' about you

50:35.500 --> 50:38.210
♪ Somethin' about you

50:38.410 --> 50:39.210
- Come on.
- Hey!

50:39.410 --> 50:40.650
No, you're not doing yourself

50:40.850 --> 50:43.600
any favors sitting
here drowning, okay?

50:45.250 --> 50:47.440
- I'll never forgive myself
for what I did to you.

50:47.640 --> 50:48.480
- You know that?
- Hardin-

50:48.680 --> 50:50.140
Never.

50:50.340 --> 50:51.700
- James posted it.
- Yeah-

50:51.900 --> 50:53.700
It was a long time ago.

50:56.440 --> 50:58.020
So you're fine now?

50:58.220 --> 50:59.360
You're fine?

50:59.560 --> 51:01.240
- I have good days,
I have bad days.

51:01.440 --> 51:03.660
I've moved on.

51:04.710 --> 51:06.230
- And so should you.
- Yeah.

51:07.890 --> 51:12.600
[girls chattering]
[melancholy music]

51:12.790 --> 51:16.020
[radio playing continues]

51:17.070 --> 51:21.860
♪ Somethin' about you

51:24.340 --> 51:25.560
♪ Somethin' about you

51:25.760 --> 51:28.440
[gentle music]

51:28.640 --> 51:30.050
- I love this.
- What?

51:30.250 --> 51:31.130
This, us.

51:33.690 --> 51:35.230
And we're always
gonna be like this,

51:35.430 --> 51:37.230
you know that, don't you?

51:37.430 --> 51:39.870
[upbeat music]

51:43.400 --> 51:45.800
♪ Somethin' about you

51:46.000 --> 51:47.760
♪ Oh

51:47.960 --> 51:49.370
♪ I don't know what
else I can say ♪

51:49.570 --> 51:50.370
[Nathalie] Woo wee!

51:50.570 --> 51:53.710
♪ Somethin' about you

51:54.540 --> 51:57.720
[indistinct singing]

51:58.720 --> 52:01.210
♪ Oh, oh

52:01.410 --> 52:03.720
[Freya giggling]

52:11.340 --> 52:12.610
- You like to fuck
with girls, right?

52:12.810 --> 52:13.660
How 'bout I fuck with you?

52:13.860 --> 52:17.440
[girls exclaiming]
[head banging]

52:17.640 --> 52:19.000
[Girls] Sebastian!

52:21.310 --> 52:24.140
[girls clamoring]

52:26.400 --> 52:28.540
[fists thudding]

52:28.740 --> 52:30.590
[Hardin grunts]
[pensive music]

52:30.790 --> 52:35.540
[solemn music]
[kicks thudding]

52:37.540 --> 52:42.150
[shouting fades]
[music continues]

52:45.550 --> 52:47.690
Get up, you little shit!

52:47.890 --> 52:50.340
[music continues]

52:58.740 --> 53:01.560
[cell door slams]

53:02.440 --> 53:05.100
[music fades]

53:05.300 --> 53:07.280
[inmates chattering]

53:07.470 --> 53:10.180
[melancholy music]

53:14.490 --> 53:17.010
- And the thought
of you leaving,

53:18.490 --> 53:21.680
it's just getting pretty
dark in here, Tess.

53:21.880 --> 53:24.630
[music continues]

53:28.500 --> 53:30.810
[Tessa] I'm here with you.

53:32.640 --> 53:33.870
[air whooshing]

53:34.070 --> 53:37.350
[keys jingling]
[cell door clanging]

53:37.550 --> 53:39.920
[door creaks]
[pensive music]

53:40.120 --> 53:43.310
- [Christian] Just
when I thought it
couldn't get any worse.

53:43.510 --> 53:46.650
[inmates chattering]

53:51.220 --> 53:52.440
Guess I'm over achiever.

53:53.310 --> 53:56.100
[solemn music]

54:02.320 --> 54:07.020
[keys jingling]
[cell door clangs]

54:08.460 --> 54:10.380
So, how'd you find me, Dad?

54:10.580 --> 54:11.500
Your mom told me.

54:13.070 --> 54:14.430
Apparently she got a
call from a young lady

54:14.630 --> 54:16.250
that you've been
spending some time with.

54:17.340 --> 54:18.210
Nathalie.

54:19.380 --> 54:20.650
We're not...

54:20.850 --> 54:21.960
- She knows it's not-
- No, no,

54:22.160 --> 54:23.000
I didn't think it was.

54:23.200 --> 54:23.950
I just...

54:25.170 --> 54:26.480
I suppose a part
of me hoped that-

54:26.680 --> 54:28.400
Oh, you hoped.

54:28.600 --> 54:31.230
You hoped that I was finally
fucking someone new didn't you?

54:31.430 --> 54:32.360
No.

54:32.560 --> 54:33.970
Yeah, you did.

54:34.170 --> 54:35.710
- God, you can twist
things around, can't you?

54:35.910 --> 54:37.540
Poor Hardin.

54:37.740 --> 54:41.020
The miserable drunk little
victim sitting at home.

54:41.220 --> 54:43.240
Honestly, I mean, I'm
surprised that you're not

54:43.440 --> 54:45.460
even embarrassed by
yourself at this point.

54:45.660 --> 54:48.420
It's pathetic.
[Hardin scoffs]

54:48.620 --> 54:51.990
I was hoping that you've maybe
come away, you've moved on,

54:52.190 --> 54:53.890
started a clean slate, maybe?

54:55.900 --> 54:56.900
Move forward.

54:58.460 --> 55:00.210
[Christian sighs]

55:00.410 --> 55:01.480
Lanny gave me this.

55:01.680 --> 55:03.610
He's been trying to
get through to you.

55:03.810 --> 55:06.520
[envelope rustling]

55:07.650 --> 55:09.180
- I am trying, you know?
- Yeah, yeah.

55:09.380 --> 55:10.400
I am.

55:10.600 --> 55:11.400
I'm fucking trying.

55:11.600 --> 55:12.910
Look at yourself.

55:14.740 --> 55:16.050
Why do you think I came here?

55:17.530 --> 55:19.060
I came here in the first place

55:19.260 --> 55:22.410
to try and resolve my past
so I can move forward.

55:22.610 --> 55:23.660
I am fucking trying.

55:30.190 --> 55:35.290
[gentle music]
[water splashing]

55:35.490 --> 55:36.890
Maybe I need to try harder.

55:39.980 --> 55:42.600
I just don't think I'll ever
move on, even if she has.

55:42.800 --> 55:43.560
Has she?

55:43.760 --> 55:45.130
She says so.

55:45.330 --> 55:46.510
So, you've talked to her?

55:49.250 --> 55:50.690
- It's mostly been one-sided.

55:52.210 --> 55:53.790
She replied to the
last message saying,

55:53.990 --> 55:56.130
"You should move
on, 'cause I have."

55:57.780 --> 55:59.450
I know you are gonna say,
I'm being irrational when...

55:59.650 --> 56:03.280
And I should just let
go but I genuinely,

56:03.480 --> 56:05.670
I cannot comprehend the
thought of giving up on us.

56:05.870 --> 56:07.630
It doesn't make sense to me.

56:07.830 --> 56:08.970
Maybe you don't have to.

56:11.410 --> 56:13.550
Maybe you can hold a space
for her in your heart

56:13.750 --> 56:15.190
like I hold a
space for your mom.

56:16.760 --> 56:18.200
Always.

56:18.400 --> 56:19.680
It doesn't mean
that you can't go on

56:19.880 --> 56:21.370
to have other great loves,

56:22.640 --> 56:23.810
and live a full life.

56:26.810 --> 56:28.080
I don't know.

56:28.280 --> 56:32.600
- Well, take it from
someone who does.

56:37.480 --> 56:42.390
It's easy to believe that our
ability to love is finite,

56:44.000 --> 56:46.010
especially when your
heart is broken.

56:47.440 --> 56:51.580
But believe it or not,
slowly you will heal.

56:53.880 --> 56:58.240
And your capacity for love
will grow exponentially.

56:58.440 --> 57:00.990
You'll be able to keep a
space for Tessa in your heart,

57:01.190 --> 57:03.820
for your family, for
your future children,

57:04.020 --> 57:05.590
for anybody who
comes into your life.

57:06.810 --> 57:08.040
And you never know,

57:08.240 --> 57:11.030
maybe you and Tessa are
meant to be together.

57:12.080 --> 57:13.390
And if that is the case,

57:13.590 --> 57:15.130
then you will find your
way back to each other,

57:15.330 --> 57:17.390
but it's not gonna
happen like this is it?

57:17.590 --> 57:18.390
Look at you.

57:19.820 --> 57:21.690
You go on drinking and
messing up the way you are.

57:26.440 --> 57:27.260
You're right.

57:29.920 --> 57:31.930
You are, of course you're right.

57:32.130 --> 57:35.190
You know, my life was
finally getting somewhere.

57:35.390 --> 57:37.890
You know, with the book I
actually finally did something,

57:38.090 --> 57:39.230
something I was proud of.

57:41.150 --> 57:42.770
And then, yeah, I mean,

57:42.970 --> 57:45.070
I guess it fucked up and
everything blew up in my face.

57:45.270 --> 57:46.600
And now the bar's
so fucking high,

57:46.800 --> 57:48.070
I'll never get back there again.

57:49.070 --> 57:50.460
I'm so scared of failing,

57:52.380 --> 57:54.470
so I just end up ruining
everything instead.

57:59.860 --> 58:00.830
It's pathetic.

58:01.030 --> 58:01.870
- You're right.
- Listen to me.

58:02.070 --> 58:02.870
It's fucking pathetic,

58:03.070 --> 58:04.530
- isn't it?
- Listen.

58:04.730 --> 58:09.100
You need to change the metrics
by which you define success.

58:09.300 --> 58:13.450
You can start by
writing one page a day.

58:13.650 --> 58:16.110
Just that, and that'll
be your success.

58:16.300 --> 58:17.980
And if your second book
comes out and it flunks,

58:18.180 --> 58:20.940
but you've been
real and authentic,

58:21.140 --> 58:22.100
then that is a success.

58:24.580 --> 58:28.600
Whether you end up with a
woman you have loved or not,

58:28.800 --> 58:31.560
you have loved with
every cell in your being,

58:31.760 --> 58:34.510
and that in and of itself
is a spectacular success.

58:40.600 --> 58:41.430
Wow.

58:43.950 --> 58:45.650
You're not bad at
this Dad stuff.

58:47.950 --> 58:50.910
- Now that for me is
the pinnacle of success.

58:53.700 --> 58:54.700
So, what are you gonna do?

58:57.270 --> 59:00.530
Could book a return flight
with me if you want.

59:02.010 --> 59:02.930
No.

59:07.360 --> 59:08.190
Thanks.

59:09.450 --> 59:11.030
I'm gonna stay here for awhile.

59:11.230 --> 59:14.370
Might sort things
through and try to write.

59:20.730 --> 59:21.810
I love you, Son.

59:24.380 --> 59:25.210
Really love you.

59:27.560 --> 59:28.390
I always have.

59:29.820 --> 59:30.650
Always will.

59:33.780 --> 59:36.140
Now, let's get some
food you fuckin' idiot.

59:36.340 --> 59:41.140
[hopeful music]
[water splashing]

59:46.620 --> 59:49.580
[inspirational music]

01:00:27.010 --> 01:00:30.010
[alcohol sloshing]

01:00:34.670 --> 01:00:39.500
[music continues]
[singer vocalizing]

01:00:52.690 --> 01:00:55.040
[bell ringing]

01:00:59.870 --> 01:01:00.700
Nathalie.

01:01:02.920 --> 01:01:04.140
Sorry for dropping

01:01:04.340 --> 01:01:05.800
- by uninvited.
- Good to see you.

01:01:06.000 --> 01:01:08.540
- [Nathalie] It's just,
I rang the doorbell

01:01:08.740 --> 01:01:09.840
and you weren't on WhatsApp

01:01:10.040 --> 01:01:11.370
and I just wanted to
see if you're okay.

01:01:11.570 --> 01:01:12.720
I'm fine.

01:01:12.920 --> 01:01:14.460
- Should we sit?
- Yes.

01:01:14.660 --> 01:01:16.980
- I brought you a
little care package.

01:01:17.180 --> 01:01:19.670
I didn't think that you'd
be in a state to go out, so.

01:01:21.320 --> 01:01:23.630
This is ridiculously generous.

01:01:26.200 --> 01:01:28.820
I should probably tell you
that I've stopped drinking.

01:01:29.020 --> 01:01:30.430
- No.
- Yeah [chuckles].

01:01:30.630 --> 01:01:31.950
- I'm sorry, that's bad.
- It would've

01:01:32.150 --> 01:01:33.290
been very thoughtful.

01:01:34.470 --> 01:01:35.640
I'll have the chocolate.

01:01:38.600 --> 01:01:41.620
- Oh, Seb is an asshole for
attacking you like that.

01:01:41.810 --> 01:01:42.570
I'm so sorry.

01:01:42.770 --> 01:01:43.700
He had his reasons.

01:01:43.900 --> 01:01:45.230
I really do wish
there was something

01:01:45.430 --> 01:01:46.840
I could do to make it up to you.

01:01:47.040 --> 01:01:51.670
- Hardin, your apology,
spending this time together,

01:01:51.870 --> 01:01:53.580
seeing that you've changed,
that all means something.

01:01:53.780 --> 01:01:56.370
You didn't force me
to do anything.

01:01:56.570 --> 01:01:59.670
No, but I lied to you, Nat.

01:02:03.320 --> 01:02:05.930
I didn't see it then,
but I do see it now.

01:02:08.420 --> 01:02:09.240
So, I'm sorry.

01:02:12.200 --> 01:02:13.040
[sighs] Oh, sorry.

01:02:13.240 --> 01:02:14.000
Does that hurt still?

01:02:14.190 --> 01:02:15.000
Oh, okay, sorry.

01:02:15.200 --> 01:02:16.000
It does hurt.

01:02:16.200 --> 01:02:17.260
- It's fine.
- I'm sorry.

01:02:17.460 --> 01:02:18.830
- Okay?
- Yeah.

01:02:19.030 --> 01:02:24.080
Oh, no.

01:02:27.350 --> 01:02:29.520
- I'm sorry.
- No, it's fine.

01:02:31.390 --> 01:02:32.570
I'm still in love with Tessa.

01:02:34.050 --> 01:02:38.360
I know she may have
moved on, but I haven't.

01:02:39.840 --> 01:02:42.550
I do want you to know
how grateful I am though,

01:02:42.740 --> 01:02:46.150
for really giving me the chance
to put what I did behind us.

01:02:47.150 --> 01:02:48.330
I think it takes
a lot of bravery

01:02:48.530 --> 01:02:52.560
to be so forgiving,
so thank you.

01:02:52.750 --> 01:02:55.550
You really deserve someone who
can give you all of themself.

01:02:56.810 --> 01:02:57.860
You really do.

01:02:59.340 --> 01:03:00.510
You're right, I do.

01:03:04.430 --> 01:03:05.570
You do.

01:03:05.770 --> 01:03:07.350
[Nathalie laughs]

01:03:07.550 --> 01:03:09.010
I think you should take
this wine back, though.

01:03:09.210 --> 01:03:10.090
I do.

01:03:10.290 --> 01:03:11.490
Let's not waste it.

01:03:11.690 --> 01:03:12.830
- It does look
very nice, though.

01:03:15.090 --> 01:03:16.490
- Yeah, I'll enjoy
that by myself.

01:03:16.690 --> 01:03:17.840
Please do.

01:03:18.040 --> 01:03:20.020
[Nathalie laughs]
[Hardin chuckles]

01:03:20.220 --> 01:03:22.150
[phone ringing]

01:03:22.350 --> 01:03:23.330
[Landon] Hey, it's Landon.

01:03:23.520 --> 01:03:24.760
Leave a message.

01:03:24.960 --> 01:03:26.460
[phone beeps]

01:03:26.660 --> 01:03:27.720
Shit.

01:03:27.920 --> 01:03:28.900
Sorry, Landon, I didn't realize

01:03:29.100 --> 01:03:30.940
what time it was over there.
I just...

01:03:31.140 --> 01:03:32.630
Just calling to say
congratulations.

01:03:34.280 --> 01:03:36.200
Wouldn't miss my brother's
wedding for the world.

01:03:37.110 --> 01:03:38.200
I love you,

01:03:39.900 --> 01:03:41.130
but don't quote me on that.

01:03:41.330 --> 01:03:46.380
[phone beeps]
[upbeat music]

01:03:55.130 --> 01:03:58.450
♪ We spend so, so
long sorting these ♪

01:03:58.650 --> 01:04:03.440
♪ And it's been 24
months now to the day ♪

01:04:04.660 --> 01:04:09.330
♪ Even though your
heart's still golden ♪

01:04:09.530 --> 01:04:13.630
♪ Somethin' else in
you seen a chance ♪

01:04:22.290 --> 01:04:27.080
♪ Well, you can let the wind
blow in any one direction ♪

01:04:28.340 --> 01:04:32.000
♪ I know I'm gonna
see you again ♪

01:04:32.200 --> 01:04:34.480
♪ And we can trade secrets

01:04:34.680 --> 01:04:38.840
♪ Maybe we can get back
to how it used to be ♪

01:04:39.040 --> 01:04:42.360
♪ Before it all began

01:04:42.560 --> 01:04:44.620
♪ Hold my arm to ya

01:04:44.820 --> 01:04:47.150
♪ [indistinct]

01:04:47.350 --> 01:04:51.810
♪ Same story but
a different day ♪

01:04:52.000 --> 01:04:56.290
♪ Keep your hand [indistinct]

01:04:56.490 --> 01:05:00.600
♪ Everyone's got
a different pace ♪

01:05:00.800 --> 01:05:03.500
[music continues]

01:05:10.600 --> 01:05:12.520
♪ And time's got surprises
you won't believe ♪

01:05:12.720 --> 01:05:14.870
♪ While you makin'
friends I'm an enemy ♪

01:05:15.070 --> 01:05:19.870
♪ Then other times it's
the other way around ♪

01:05:20.690 --> 01:05:22.700
[music continues]

01:05:33.320 --> 01:05:35.710
♪ Yeah, yeah

01:05:37.320 --> 01:05:39.640
Just that green one.

01:05:39.830 --> 01:05:41.160
Thank you.

01:05:41.360 --> 01:05:43.470
Keep the change.

01:05:43.660 --> 01:05:44.470
[Hardin speaking in Portuguese]

01:05:44.670 --> 01:05:47.300
[worker speaking in Portuguese]

01:05:47.490 --> 01:05:48.640
They all look beautiful.

01:05:48.840 --> 01:05:50.080
They all suit you
but I just think

01:05:50.280 --> 01:05:52.680
that the second one is very you.

01:05:53.990 --> 01:05:57.040
- Yes.
- It fits you perfectly.

01:05:57.240 --> 01:05:58.920
But there's a couple
more over here

01:05:59.120 --> 01:06:00.920
- if you wanna just have a look.
- Okay.

01:06:01.120 --> 01:06:02.050
Hey.

01:06:02.250 --> 01:06:03.560
[Nathalie] Hey.

01:06:05.040 --> 01:06:07.130
So, is this goodbye?

01:06:08.660 --> 01:06:09.570
I fly tomorrow.

01:06:11.180 --> 01:06:12.620
I just came back
to give you this.

01:06:17.970 --> 01:06:19.500
It's still very much
a work in progress.

01:06:19.700 --> 01:06:21.110
I haven't sent it
to my editor yet

01:06:21.310 --> 01:06:22.630
or anything like that, so.

01:06:22.830 --> 01:06:24.630
- Don't worry,
I'm sure it's brilliant.

01:06:25.370 --> 01:06:27.540
And if it isn't I'll just
pretend it is [smirks].

01:06:29.420 --> 01:06:31.810
It's just [sighs],

01:06:36.380 --> 01:06:37.550
you're in it,

01:06:39.860 --> 01:06:41.390
and I just wanna make sure
that you're entirely okay

01:06:41.590 --> 01:06:43.790
with everything in
there before I send it

01:06:43.990 --> 01:06:46.000
to my publisher or anyone
else [inhales shakily].

01:06:48.000 --> 01:06:49.780
Oh, so you want my permission?

01:06:52.220 --> 01:06:54.320
[chuckles] I guess I'm trying

01:06:54.520 --> 01:06:55.620
to learn from my old mistakes.

01:06:58.710 --> 01:07:00.280
- Well, I look
forward to reading it.

01:07:00.480 --> 01:07:03.010
[gentle music]

01:07:05.630 --> 01:07:07.630
Have a safe flight, okay?

01:07:10.500 --> 01:07:13.240
[Hardin exhales]

01:07:15.200 --> 01:07:16.780
Bye, Nathalie.

01:07:16.980 --> 01:07:21.420
[light music]
[seagulls squawking]

01:08:20.180 --> 01:08:22.880
[waves splashing]

01:08:57.170 --> 01:09:00.130
[music intensifying]

01:09:38.560 --> 01:09:41.220
[music softens]

01:09:49.880 --> 01:09:54.750
[airplane engine humming]
[passengers chattering]

01:09:58.930 --> 01:10:01.630
[phone vibrating]

01:10:11.420 --> 01:10:13.810
[phone beeps]

01:10:25.650 --> 01:10:30.440
[Nathalie exhales]
[gentle music]

01:10:32.660 --> 01:10:35.360
[keys jingling]

01:10:41.670 --> 01:10:43.370
[Nathalie] You see that?

01:10:43.570 --> 01:10:44.800
That is my dream.

01:10:51.980 --> 01:10:56.680
[keys jingling]
[music continues]

01:11:03.780 --> 01:11:08.480
[leaves rustling]
[soft music]

01:11:19.710 --> 01:11:21.240
You look stunning.

01:11:21.440 --> 01:11:23.760
Such a beautiful bride.

01:11:23.960 --> 01:11:26.150
- I still can't believe
how fast this days come.

01:11:27.930 --> 01:11:29.450
- [Nora] What if
he doesn't show up?

01:11:30.980 --> 01:11:32.600
- Ken drove him
here this morning.

01:11:32.800 --> 01:11:34.380
He would've alerted us
if there was a concern.

01:11:34.580 --> 01:11:36.210
- [Tessa] And it's
Landon, he would never.

01:11:36.410 --> 01:11:39.210
[fist knocks]

01:11:39.410 --> 01:11:40.470
Hope I'm not intruding.

01:11:41.470 --> 01:11:42.910
Thanks.

01:11:43.110 --> 01:11:45.910
- [Man] Also, the caterer's
havin' a minor meltdown.

01:11:46.110 --> 01:11:47.730
- Can you tell her
I'll be a minute?

01:11:48.390 --> 01:11:49.340
I can try.

01:11:50.870 --> 01:11:52.270
[Tessa] Okay.

01:11:52.470 --> 01:11:54.970
- I am sure Landon is just
as nervous as you are,

01:11:55.170 --> 01:11:57.400
but between Ken and Hardin-

01:11:57.600 --> 01:11:59.010
Oh, if Hardin's helping

01:11:59.210 --> 01:12:00.570
I should just cancel
the honeymoon now.

01:12:03.530 --> 01:12:05.670
You know, if he wasn't
Landon's brother,

01:12:05.870 --> 01:12:08.320
he wouldn't have been invited,
much less the best man.

01:12:09.800 --> 01:12:12.190
I'm gonna go check on things.

01:12:15.370 --> 01:12:17.940
- So what's it been, two
years since you've seen him?

01:12:19.810 --> 01:12:21.690
25 months, but who's counting?

01:12:21.890 --> 01:12:24.080
[fist knocks]

01:12:24.280 --> 01:12:25.430
Hey, Tess?

01:12:25.630 --> 01:12:27.830
- Yeah, okay, coming.
- Okay.

01:12:28.030 --> 01:12:30.830
[door closes]

01:12:31.030 --> 01:12:32.470
- [Tessa] You
ready, Mrs. Gibson?

01:12:33.820 --> 01:12:38.520
- No, but I will be
as soon as I see him.

01:12:39.390 --> 01:12:40.350
Are you?

01:12:41.960 --> 01:12:46.970
Yeah, of course.

01:12:52.060 --> 01:12:54.720
[Landon exhales nervously]
[light instrumental music]

01:12:54.920 --> 01:12:56.380
Last chance to bail.

01:12:56.580 --> 01:12:58.250
Me, bail?

01:12:58.450 --> 01:13:00.890
You're the one who's
nervous about seeing her.

01:13:01.630 --> 01:13:02.590
I'm not nervous.

01:13:03.370 --> 01:13:04.380
I'm fine.

01:13:05.590 --> 01:13:07.130
You're fine?

01:13:07.330 --> 01:13:09.210
- She's the maid of honor,
I figured she'd show.

01:13:09.410 --> 01:13:11.040
Okay, hot stuff.

01:13:11.240 --> 01:13:12.260
Go talk to her.

01:13:12.460 --> 01:13:14.990
[soft violin music]

01:13:20.650 --> 01:13:22.360
[Landon exhales nervously]

01:13:22.560 --> 01:13:25.180
[gentle music]

01:13:53.210 --> 01:13:56.700
- You really do have
an eye for this stuff.

01:13:56.900 --> 01:13:57.650
Thank you.

01:13:57.850 --> 01:14:00.610
[music continues]

01:14:15.620 --> 01:14:18.060
[soft music]

01:15:25.250 --> 01:15:27.310
[upbeat music]
[singer singing]

01:15:27.510 --> 01:15:28.350
[Robert speaking indistinctly]

01:15:28.550 --> 01:15:31.260
[Tessa laughs]

01:15:33.390 --> 01:15:34.450
There he is.

01:15:34.650 --> 01:15:35.670
[Hardin] Hey.

01:15:35.870 --> 01:15:36.840
Hey.

01:15:37.040 --> 01:15:38.060
You all right?

01:15:38.260 --> 01:15:39.970
Yeah, I'm fine.

01:15:40.170 --> 01:15:43.140
[Tessa speaking faintly]

01:15:47.930 --> 01:15:49.290
Tell him.

01:15:49.490 --> 01:15:51.460
- I am enjoying this
way too much to put him

01:15:51.660 --> 01:15:52.330
out of his misery.

01:15:52.530 --> 01:15:53.680
[Christian] Have mercy.

01:15:53.880 --> 01:15:54.720
Enjoying what?

01:15:56.020 --> 01:15:56.940
What?

01:15:57.940 --> 01:15:59.160
They're not together.

01:16:01.160 --> 01:16:02.520
- Landon said
they're inseparable.

01:16:02.720 --> 01:16:05.160
Yeah, like brother and sister.

01:16:08.430 --> 01:16:10.050
- Are you sure?
- Yeah, no, no-

01:16:10.250 --> 01:16:12.090
- He's dating a
literal neuroscientist

01:16:12.290 --> 01:16:14.270
and apparently they're already
talking about marriage,

01:16:14.470 --> 01:16:15.580
so yes, I am sure.

01:16:15.770 --> 01:16:18.440
[singer singing]

01:16:34.670 --> 01:16:36.250
Hey.

01:16:36.450 --> 01:16:38.160
I need a favor.

01:16:38.360 --> 01:16:43.160
[upbeat music]
[Tessa chuckles]

01:16:43.900 --> 01:16:45.250
Tessa, wanna go dance?

01:16:46.990 --> 01:16:48.170
- Yeah.
- Yes, she does.

01:16:48.370 --> 01:16:49.000
Yeah, sure.

01:16:49.200 --> 01:16:51.820
[Landon laughs]

01:16:58.220 --> 01:17:02.540
♪ You know I need ya

01:17:02.730 --> 01:17:04.670
♪ Know I need ya

01:17:04.870 --> 01:17:06.320
♪ I need ya

01:17:06.520 --> 01:17:10.330
♪ Oh, my love

01:17:10.520 --> 01:17:12.230
♪ Oh

01:17:13.890 --> 01:17:16.290
- Thought I'd save you.
- Hey.

01:17:16.490 --> 01:17:17.240
He's a bit short.

01:17:18.670 --> 01:17:19.990
Terrible dancer, too.

01:17:20.190 --> 01:17:22.680
[gentle music]

01:17:23.940 --> 01:17:25.460
He told me you bribed him.

01:17:31.470 --> 01:17:36.180
♪ Sleep walkin'
without knowin' ♪

01:17:36.380 --> 01:17:39.620
♪ Gave up fightin' the river

01:17:39.820 --> 01:17:42.360
♪ Watching the madness

01:17:42.560 --> 01:17:45.660
♪ I can see much more

01:17:47.050 --> 01:17:48.440
You look well.

01:17:52.100 --> 01:17:53.010
Well?

01:17:54.840 --> 01:17:57.800
- Good, handsome,
very hot [chuckles].

01:18:04.330 --> 01:18:07.500
- You are always the most
beautiful woman in the room.

01:18:14.080 --> 01:18:15.290
I owe you an apology.

01:18:16.730 --> 01:18:19.000
I never meant to
publicly embarrass you

01:18:19.200 --> 01:18:20.310
after writing "After,"

01:18:20.510 --> 01:18:22.530
- and I'm so sorry.
- I know, I know.

01:18:22.730 --> 01:18:24.360
- It was wrong to publish
it without your permission

01:18:24.560 --> 01:18:26.010
and I know that now.

01:18:26.210 --> 01:18:28.700
I really hurt you,
Tess, and I'm sorry.

01:18:32.180 --> 01:18:33.310
I'm really proud of you.

01:18:36.920 --> 01:18:37.840
Thank you.

01:18:38.930 --> 01:18:41.930
♪ With hearts beating

01:18:43.370 --> 01:18:47.160
- [Woman] Will everyone
please take your seats?

01:18:47.360 --> 01:18:49.330
It's time for the toasts.

01:18:52.200 --> 01:18:54.650
For my 21st.

01:18:54.850 --> 01:18:55.680
It's the only one.

01:19:00.120 --> 01:19:00.990
Hardin?

01:19:06.950 --> 01:19:09.440
- You know I almost didn't
take this best man gig

01:19:09.640 --> 01:19:11.530
because I knew I'd
have to do this

01:19:11.730 --> 01:19:14.620
and gush about my feelings
for the two of you.

01:19:14.820 --> 01:19:17.190
And we all know I hate
to divulge these days.

01:19:17.390 --> 01:19:19.500
[guests chuckling]

01:19:19.700 --> 01:19:21.630
All right, get to the point.

01:19:21.830 --> 01:19:23.070
[guests chuckling]

01:19:23.270 --> 01:19:24.490
When I first met Landon,

01:19:25.970 --> 01:19:28.460
- I instantly hated him.
- Oh boy.

01:19:28.660 --> 01:19:30.770
- And I was jealous.
He had everything I ever
wanted in life.

01:19:30.970 --> 01:19:32.860
He has a loving family, I mean,

01:19:33.060 --> 01:19:34.370
he had plans for his future.

01:19:35.770 --> 01:19:38.870
And well, now, now
he has a beautiful,

01:19:39.060 --> 01:19:40.730
